  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Financial Modeling & Valuation:</strong> Create, analyze, and audit complex valuation models in Excel (e.g., DCF, LBO, comparable company analysis).</li><li><strong>Transaction Execution:</strong> Manage day-to-day workstreams for M&A and capital raising deals, including due diligence and coordinating with internal/external parties.</li><li><strong>Pitch Materials & Presentations:</strong> Prepare PowerPoint-based pitch books, CIMs (Confidential Information Memoranda), and marketing materials for clients.</li><li><strong>Project Management & Mentorship:</strong> Supervise and review the work of junior analysts, ensuring accuracy and managing timelines for multiple projects.</li><li><strong>Client Interaction:</strong> Participate in client meetings, management interviews, and Q&A sessions. </li><li><li><strong>Financial Reporting & Analysis:</strong> Prepare financial statements, analyze data, identify trends, and create reports for management.</li><li><strong>Budgeting & Forecasting:</strong> Assist in creating budgets, forecasting financial performance, and tracking performance against goals.</li><li><strong>Operations & Transactions:</strong> Manage invoices, process payments (AP/AR), reconcile bank statements, and handle expense reports.</li><li><strong>Compliance & Auditing:</strong> Ensure adherence to regulations, assist with tax filings (GST, income tax), and support external audits.</li><li><strong>System Support:</strong> Help with implementing new accounting software and maintaining financial records.</li><li><strong>Internal Support:</strong> Provide financial guidance and support to other departments, advising on fiscal procedures. </li></li></ul>",
